headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 27 points, Malik Beasley added 20 and the Milwaukee Bucks overcame a 37-point effort from LaMelo Ball to beat the Charlotte Hornets 130-99 on Friday night and remain unbeaten in NBA In-Season Tournament play.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 27, leads 3-point barrage as Bucks beat Hornets to remain unbeaten in tourney play

events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — New York Knicks coach Tom Thibodeau is treating the NBA In-Season Tournament the same way he approaches other games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks beat Washington 120-99; Wizards out of contention in NBA In-Season Tournament

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 32 points, seven rebounds and eight assists and the Philadelphia 76ers put away the Atlanta Hawks 126-116 on Friday night in an NBA In-Season Tournament game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid goes for 32 as 76ers win NBA In-Season Tournament Game over Hawks

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had a season-high 28 points and Evan Mobley and Max Strus scored 18 apiece as the Cleveland Cavaliers beat Detroit 108-100 in an NBA In-Season Tournament game on Friday night, handing the Pistons their 10th consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 28 points for the Cavaliers in a 108-100 win over Pistons in tournament play

headlines.description: — Derrick White made a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 26.8 seconds remaining in the fourth quarter and the Boston Celtics recovered after blowing a 16-point halftime lead to beat the Toronto Raptors 108-105 in an NBA In-Season Tournament game on Friday...
headlines.shortLinkText: White hits tiebreaking 3, Celtics hold on to beat Raptors 108-105 in tournament game

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Sacramento Kings All-Star De’Aaron Fox celebrated playing in the In-Season Tournament with his finest game of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox's season-high 43 leads Kings past Wembanyama, Spurs 129-120 in in-season tourney

headlines.description: — The Orlando Magic held the Chicago Bulls to 33 points in the first half once again and watched their lead slip away after going up by 19.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 21 as Magic beat Bulls 103-97 after blowing another 19-point lead

events.name: Denver Nuggets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — New Orleans stars Zion Williamson and Brandon Ingram helped put Denver in a 20-point hole and also came through in the final minutes to stop Nikola Jokic and Co. from climbing all the way back.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson and Ingram come through late to lift Pelicans past Nuggets 115-110

headlines.description: — The Phoenix Suns have opted to go without a traditional point guard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 38 and Booker has a career-best 15 assists to boost the Suns past the Jazz

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — LeBron James matched his season-high with 35 points and the Los Angeles Lakers handed the Portland Trail Blazers their sixth straight loss with a 107-95 victory in an In-Season Tournament game on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James has 35 and Lakers stay atop In-Season Tournament group with 107-95 win at Portland

headlines.description: — James Harden hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer while getting fouled with six seconds to play, sending the Los Angeles Clippers to their first victory since his arrival with a 106-100 win over the Houston Rockets on Friday night in the NBA In-Season...
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden's tiebreaking 4-point play snaps Clippers' 6-game skid, beats Rockets 106-100
